name: Bulbasaur
info: It is one of the three First partner Pokémon that can be chosen in the Kanto region.

name: Ivysaur
info: Pokémon introduced in Generation I. It evolves from Bulbasaur starting at level 16 and evolves into Venusaur starting at level 32.

name: Venusaur
info: It is the mascot for Pokémon Green and Pokémon LeafGreen and the final form of Bulbasaur.

name: Charmander
info: Along with Bulbasaur and Squirtle, Charmander is one of three starter Pokémon of Kanto available at the beginning of Pokémon Red, Green, Blue, FireRed, and LeafGreen.

name: Charmeleon
info: Charmeleon is a small, bipedal, dinosaur-like Pokémon with an appearance similar to that of its pre-evolved form, Charmander.

name: Charizard
info: It can Mega Evolve into either Mega Charizard X, using the Charizardite X or Mega Charizard Y, using the Charizardite Y. It has a Gigantamax form. Mega Charizard X has its Flying changed into Dragon-typing. It is the mascot for Pokémon Red and its remake, Pokémon FireRed.

name: Squirtle
info: It evolves into Wartortle starting at level 16. It is one of the three First partner Pokémon that can be chosen in Kanto region.

name: Wartortle
info: It is the evolved form of Squirtle. They use water to cloak themselves before attacking prey and swiftly swimming after them, using their ears and tails to balance themselves.

name: Blastoise
info: Blastoise is the evolved form of Wartortle, and the final evolution of Squirtle. It is also the version mascot for Pokémon Blue. It has a Mega Evolution and a Gigantamax form. Blastoise can take the role of a leader in large groups of Squirtle and Wartortle. Its preferred habitat seems to be freshwater ponds and lakes. Blastoise are watchful Pokémon. They dislike humans in their territory, but will not attack unless provoked. They tend to fight when they sense danger.

name: Caterpie
info: Caterpie are known for their great appetites, usually eating many leaves before creating cocoons to evolve. They use self-made silk to both produce cocoons for evolution. As weak, soft-bodied Pokémon, Caterpie attempt to gather as much energy as possible to hasten their evolutions into Metapod, and afterwards into Butterfree.

name: Metapod
info: To avoid attacks, these Pokémon stay motionless and simply ​wait. Metapod are remarkably patient, enduring whatever pain they must to reach their final stages. They must remain upright while biding their time or risk spilling out their innards.

name: Butterfree
info: Butterfree is an insect-like Pokémon appearing as a large butterfly. In its Gigantamax form, Bufferfree's body has a larger frame with red glowing eyes.

name: Weedle
info: The stingers and brightly colored bodies of these Pokémon are intended to ward off potential predators who would not enjoy a mouthful of toxins. Weedle also have a sharp sense of smell, using their nose-like proboscises to sense which leaves are safe to consume.

name: Kakuna
info: Weedle seek out trees, branches or piles of leaves to hide in; when they evolve into Kakuna, their ability to move becomes severely restricted, and they can only inch about very slowly. They can sometimes be seen hanging from tree branches on strands of silk in large numbers. Kakuna can only learn Harden naturally.

name: Beedrill
info: Beedrill is extremely territorial and will attack anyone who gets too close to their hive. They are aggressive Pokémon and collectively attack the people around them.

name: Pidgey
info: Pidgey are very docile Pokémon that prefer to avoid confrontation with other Pokémon and humans altogether, hiding in tall grass to prevent themselves from being seen. If cornered, though, they will attempt to escape by using Sand Attack to blind foes or Whirlwind to blow them away and buy themselves time to fly away.

name: Pidgeotto
info: Pidgeotto has outstanding vision as it is able to distinguish its prey from high distances. It is able to carry its prey for over 60 miles.

name: Pidgeot
info: It is the evolved form of Pidgeotto, and the final evolution of Pidgey. Pidgeot is even more dangerous than its previous evolutionary stage. This is because it is bulkier and more aggressive than Pidgeotto, enabling it to catch much bigger prey. A favorite target is Magikarp, which Pidgeot can spot from a great distance.

name: Rattata
info: Rattata's teeth grow very quickly and they can survive almost anywhere. It's happy to nest just about anywhere. They also utilize their teeth so they can use attacks such as Super Fang and Bite.

name: Raticate
info: To compensate for its steadily growing teeth, Raticate gnaws on hard things such as buildings, even being able to topple them down when doing so. Also, its webbed feet allow it to swim well when it hunts.

name: Spearow
info: They are noted for being frail, for which they make up for with their Mirror Move ability. Eggs laid by Spearow are known to be prey for hungry Ekans, which are known to be able to swallow them whole.

name: Fearow
info: Fearow uses its great wings to catch air currents and effortlessly glide over large distances for as long as a day without having to land or rest. It flies high into the sky, and swoops down at its prey. By using a combination of its neck and beak, it has a long reach, allowing it to pluck bugs from the ground or easily pluck prey from soil or water as it swoops down. If it senses danger, it avoids it if possible.

name: Ekans
info: Ekans, like real snakes, have the ability to unhinge their jaws. Ekans also share other characteristics with snakes, such as using its tongue to test the air for the presence of prey and shedding its skin. An Ekans will lose its rattle once it evolves into Arbok.

name: Arbok
info: Arbok has the abilities Intimidate and Shed Skin along with the hidden ability Unnerve. Intimidate lowers the opponent's attack stat when the player enters battle while Shed Skin cures Arbok from status ailments at the end of a turn with a 30% chance. Unnerve prevents the opponent from eating its berry. A powerful constrictor, Arbok can crush a steel barrel in its mighty coils.

name: Pikachu
info: Pikachu is renowned for being the most well-known and recognizable Pokémon. Over the years, Pikachu has become so popular that it serves as the Pokémon franchise mascot. It is the Version Mascot and First partner Pokémon for the game Pokémon Yellow and its remake, Pokémon: Let's Go, Pikachu!. It is also well known from the anime, where Ash Ketchum, the former protagonist, owns a Pikachu.

name: Raichu
info: Raichu can generate electricity through its cheeks and electrocute its opponents. The highest amount of electricity it can discharge to take down its foes are 100,000 volts.

name: Sandshrew
info: Sandshrew, when in danger, can curl into a ball to defend itself. They can also claw away sharp rock that impede their digging. Alolan Sandshrew lack flexibility and cannot curl into a ball but have an excelling natural defense which makes up for this. They also have natural maneuverability on ice.

name: sandslash
info: Introduced in Generation I, and an Ice/Steel-type Pokémon introduced in Generation VII which is exclusive to Pokémon Moon. Sandslash evolves from Sandshrew at level 22, and Alolan Sandslash evolves from Alolan Sandshrew when an Ice Stone is used on it.

name: Nidoran♀
info: Nidoran♀ is a small, quadruped, rodent-like Pokémon. It is the female counterpart to Nidoran♂ and is one of the first known Pokémon capable of being either male or female.

name: Nidorina
info: Nidorina evolves from Nidoran♀ starting at level 16 and evolves into Nidoqueen when exposed to a Moon Stone.

name: Nidoqueen
info: Nidoqueen is a large, bipedal, blue Pokémon with distinct reptilian features. Its body is covered with scales, and its shoulders, lower legs, and lower jaw are adorned with pronounced spikes.

name: Nidoran♂
info: Nidoran♂ is a small, quadruped, rodent-like Pokémon. It is the male counterpart to Nidoran♀ and is one of the first known Pokémon capable of being either male or female.

name: Nidorino
info: Nidorino evolves from Nidoran♂ starting at level 16 and evolves into Nidoking when exposed to a Moon Stone.

name: Nidoking
info: Nidoking is a large, bipedal, purple Pokémon with distinct reptilian features. Its body is covered with scales, and its shoulders, lower legs, and lower jaw are adorned with pronounced spikes.

name: Clefairy
info: Clefairy is a small, round, pink, star-shaped Pokémon with a vaguely humanoid appearance. It is said to appear when the full moon shines.

name: Clefable
info: Clefable evolves from Clefairy when exposed to a Moon Stone. Clefable is known for its acute hearing and ability to walk silently.

name: Vulpix
info: Vulpix is a small, quadruped, fox-like Pokémon with a reddish-brown pelt and six orange tails.

name: Ninetales
info: Ninetales evolves from Vulpix when exposed to a Fire Stone. It is known for its nine long, luxurious tails and mystical powers.

name: Jigglypuff
info: Jigglypuff is known for its singing ability, putting its opponents to sleep with its lullabies. It evolves from Igglybuff when leveled up with high friendship and evolves into Wigglytuff when exposed to a Moon Stone.

name: Wigglytuff
info: Wigglytuff is the evolved form of Jigglypuff when exposed to a Moon Stone. Its body is very elastic, and by inhaling deeply, it can inflate itself seemingly without end.

name: Zubat
info: Zubat lives in dark caves and avoids sunlight. It evolves into Golbat starting at level 22.

name: Golbat
info: Golbat evolves from Zubat at level 22 and evolves into Crobat when leveled up with high friendship. It attacks its prey with sharp fangs and sucks their blood.

name: Oddish
info: Oddish buries itself in the soil to absorb nutrients and evolves into Gloom starting at level 21.

name: Gloom
info: Gloom evolves from Oddish at level 21 and can evolve into Vileplume when exposed to a Leaf Stone or into Bellossom when exposed to a Sun Stone.

name: Vileplume
info: Vileplume is the evolved form of Gloom when exposed to a Leaf Stone. It releases toxic spores from the petals of its large flower.

name: Paras
info: Paras is a bug and grass type Pokémon with mushrooms growing on its back. It evolves into Parasect starting at level 24.

name: Parasect
info: Parasect evolves from Paras at level 24. It is known for the large mushroom on its back, which is the result of parasitic growth.

name: Venonat
info: Venonat is covered in thick fur that is used to detect vibrations. It evolves into Venomoth starting at level 31.

name: Venomoth
info: Venomoth evolves from Venonat starting at level 31. It scatters toxic scales from its wings during battle.

name: Diglett
info: Diglett lives underground and has a tendency to pop up from the ground in unexpected places. It evolves into Dugtrio starting at level 26.

name: Dugtrio
info: Dugtrio evolves from Diglett starting at level 26. It consists of three Diglett linked together.

name: Meowth
info: Meowth is known for its love of shiny objects and coins. It evolves into Persian starting at level 28.

name: Persian
info: Persian evolves from Meowth starting at level 28. It is known for its elegance and sophisticated nature.

name: Psyduck
info: Psyduck suffers from frequent headaches that can trigger intense psychic powers. It evolves into Golduck starting at level 33.

name: Golduck
info: Golduck evolves from Psyduck starting at level 33. It is a strong swimmer and uses its psychic abilities to battle.

name: Mankey
info: Mankey is an aggressive Pokémon that becomes enraged quickly. It evolves into Primeape starting at level 28.

name: Primeape
info: Primeape evolves from Mankey starting at level 28. It is known for its uncontrollable rage.

name: Growlithe
info: Growlithe is loyal and friendly, often used as a police dog in the Pokémon world. It evolves into Arcanine when exposed to a Fire Stone.

name: Arcanine
info: Arcanine evolves from Growlithe when exposed to a Fire Stone. It is known for its speed and majestic appearance.

name: Poliwag
info: Poliwag is a tadpole Pokémon with a distinctive spiral on its belly. It evolves into Poliwhirl starting at level 25.

name: Poliwhirl
info: Poliwhirl evolves from Poliwag starting at level 25. It can evolve into either Poliwrath when exposed to a Water Stone or Politoed when traded while holding a King's Rock.

name: Poliwrath
info: Poliwrath evolves from Poliwhirl when exposed to a Water Stone. It is a skilled swimmer and fighter.

name: Abra
info: Abra is known for its ability to teleport. It evolves into Kadabra starting at level 16.

name: Kadabra
info: Kadabra evolves from Abra starting at level 16. It evolves into Alakazam when traded. Kadabra has powerful psychic abilities.

name: Alakazam
info: Alakazam evolves from Kadabra when traded. It is known for its incredible intelligence and psychic powers.

name: Machop
info: Machop is a strong and muscular Pokémon. It evolves into Machoke starting at level 28.

name: Machoke
info: Machoke evolves from Machop starting at level 28. It evolves into Machamp when traded. Machoke is known for its immense strength.

name: Machamp
info: Machamp evolves from Machoke when traded. It has four arms and is capable of throwing powerful punches.

name: Bellsprout
info: Bellsprout is a plant Pokémon with a bell-shaped flower. It evolves into Weepinbell starting at level 21.

name: Weepinbell
info: Weepinbell evolves from Bellsprout starting at level 21. It evolves into Victreebel when exposed to a Leaf Stone.

name: Victreebel
info: Victreebel evolves from Weepinbell when exposed to a Leaf Stone. It is known for its strong acid and carnivorous nature.

name: Tentacool
info: Tentacool is a jellyfish Pokémon. It evolves into Tentacruel starting at level 30.

name: Tentacruel
info: Tentacruel evolves from Tentacool starting at level 30. It has numerous tentacles and is known for its powerful poison.

name: Geodude
info: Geodude is a rock Pokémon that evolves into Graveler starting at level 25.

name: Graveler
info: Graveler evolves from Geodude starting at level 25 and evolves into Golem when traded.

name: Golem
info: Golem evolves from Graveler when traded. It has a tough, rock-like body.

name: Ponyta
info: Ponyta is a fire-type Pokémon resembling a horse. It evolves into Rapidash starting at level 40.

name: Rapidash
info: Rapidash evolves from Ponyta starting at level 40. It is known for its incredible speed and fiery mane.

name: Slowpoke
info: Slowpoke is a dual-type Water/Psychic Pokémon that evolves into Slowbro starting at level 37 or Slowking when traded holding a King's Rock.

name: Slowbro
info: Slowbro evolves from Slowpoke starting at level 37. It is known for its relaxed nature and the Shellder that clamps onto its tail.

name: Magnemite
info: Magnemite is an Electric/Steel-type Pokémon. It evolves into Magneton starting at level 30.

name: Magneton
info: Magneton evolves from Magnemite starting at level 30 and can evolve into Magnezone when leveled up in a special magnetic field.

name: Farfetch'd
info: Farfetch'd is a Normal/Flying-type Pokémon known for carrying a leek. In Galar, it evolves into Sirfetch'd after landing three critical hits in a single battle.

name: Doduo
info: Doduo is a dual-type Normal/Flying Pokémon that evolves into Dodrio starting at level 31.

name: Dodrio
info: Dodrio evolves from Doduo starting at level 31. It has three heads and is known for its incredible speed.

name: Seel
info: Seel is a Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Dewgong starting at level 34.

name: Dewgong
info: Dewgong evolves from Seel starting at level 34. It is a Water/Ice-type Pokémon known for its swimming abilities.

name: Grimer
info: Grimer is a Poison-type Pokémon that evolves into Muk starting at level 38. In Alola, it is a Poison/Dark-type.

name: Muk
info: Muk evolves from Grimer starting at level 38. In Alola, Muk is a Poison/Dark-type Pokémon.

name: Shellder
info: Shellder is a Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Cloyster when exposed to a Water Stone.

name: Cloyster
info: Cloyster evolves from Shellder when exposed to a Water Stone. It is a dual-type Water/Ice Pokémon.

name: Gastly
info: Gastly is a Ghost/Poison-type Pokémon that evolves into Haunter starting at level 25, which evolves into Gengar when traded.

name: Haunter
info: Haunter evolves from Gastly starting at level 25 and evolves into Gengar when traded. It is known for its mischievous and playful nature.

name: Gengar
info: Gengar evolves from Haunter when traded. It is known for its shadowy and elusive nature.

name: Onix
info: Onix is a Rock/Ground-type Pokémon that evolves into Steelix when traded holding a Metal Coat.

name: Drowzee
info: Drowzee is a Psychic-type Pokémon that evolves into Hypno starting at level 26. It is known for its ability to put others to sleep.

name: Hypno
info: Hypno evolves from Drowzee starting at level 26. It is a Psychic-type Pokémon known for its hypnotic abilities.

name: Krabby
info: Krabby is a Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Kingler starting at level 28. It is known for its strong pincers.

name: Kingler
info: Kingler evolves from Krabby starting at level 28. It is known for its immense pincers, which it uses to crush prey.

name: Voltorb
info: Voltorb is an Electric-type Pokémon that evolves into Electrode starting at level 30. It resembles a Poké Ball.

name: Electrode
info: Electrode evolves from Voltorb starting at level 30. It is known for its high speed and tendency to explode.

name: Exeggcute
info: Exeggcute is a Grass/Psychic-type Pokémon that evolves into Exeggutor when exposed to a Leaf Stone.

name: Exeggutor
info: Exeggutor evolves from Exeggcute when exposed to a Leaf Stone. In Alola, Exeggutor has a different form that is a Grass/Dragon-type.

name: Cubone
info: Cubone is a Ground-type Pokémon that evolves into Marowak starting at level 28. It wears the skull of its deceased mother.

name: Marowak
info: Marowak evolves from Cubone starting at level 28. In Alola, Marowak has a different form that is a Fire/Ghost-type.

name: Hitmonlee
info: Hitmonlee is a Fighting-type Pokémon that evolves from Tyrogue starting at level 20 if Tyrogue's Attack is higher than its Defense.

name: Hitmonchan
info: Hitmonchan is a Fighting-type Pokémon that evolves from Tyrogue starting at level 20 if Tyrogue's Defense is higher than its Attack.

name: Lickitung
info: Lickitung is a Normal-type Pokémon that evolves into Lickilicky when leveled up while knowing the move Rollout.

name: Koffing
info: Koffing is a Poison-type Pokémon that evolves into Weezing starting at level 35. It is known for emitting toxic gases.

name: Weezing
info: Weezing evolves from Koffing starting at level 35. It has a Galarian form that is a Poison/Fairy-type.

name: Rhyhorn
info: Rhyhorn is a Ground/Rock-type Pokémon that evolves into Rhydon starting at level 42.

name: Rhydon
info: Rhydon evolves from Rhyhorn starting at level 42 and evolves into Rhyperior when traded holding a Protector.

name: Chansey
info: Chansey is a Normal-type Pokémon that evolves from Happiny when leveled up while holding an Oval Stone during the day and evolves into Blissey when leveled up with high friendship.

name: Tangela
info: Tangela is a Grass-type Pokémon that evolves into Tangrowth when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

name: Kangaskhan
info: Kangaskhan is a Normal-type Pokémon. It does not evolve from or into any other Pokémon. It has a Mega Evolution.

name: Horsea
info: Horsea is a Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Seadra starting at level 32. It can further evolve into Kingdra when traded holding a Dragon Scale.

name: Seadra
info: Seadra evolves from Horsea starting at level 32 and evolves into Kingdra when traded holding a Dragon Scale.

name: Goldeen
info: Goldeen is a Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Seaking starting at level 33. It is known for its beauty and elegance.

name: Seaking
info: Seaking evolves from Goldeen starting at level 33. It is known for its powerful horn and swimming skills.

name: Staryu
info: Staryu is a Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Starmie when exposed to a Water Stone. It is known for its star-shaped body and ability to regenerate.

name: Starmie
info: Starmie evolves from Staryu when exposed to a Water Stone. It is known for its mystical appearance and its psychic powers.

name: Mr. Mime
info: Mr. Mime is a Psychic/Fairy-type Pokémon that is known for its ability to create invisible barriers. It evolves into Mr. Rime in later generations.

name: Scyther
info: Scyther is a Bug/Flying-type Pokémon that evolves into Scizor when traded holding a Metal Coat. It is known for its sharp scythes and agility.

name: Starmie
info: Scyther is a Bug/Flying-type Pokémon that evolves into Scizor when traded holding a Metal Coat. It is known for its sharp scythes and agility.

name: Jynx
info: Jynx is an Ice/Psychic-type Pokémon known for its chilling presence and its ability to use psychic powers. It evolves from Smoochum.

name: Electabuzz
info: Electabuzz is an Electric-type Pokémon known for its strong electric attacks. It evolves into Electivire when traded holding an Electirizer.

name: Magmar
info: Magmar is a Fire-type Pokémon known for its fiery body and intense heat. It evolves into Magmortar when traded holding a Magmarizer.

name: Pinsir
info: Pinsir is a Bug-type Pokémon known for its powerful pincers. It does not evolve from or into any other Pokémon.

name: Tauros
info: Tauros is a Normal-type Pokémon known for its aggression and strength. It has no evolutions.

name: Magikarp
info: Magikarp is a Water-type Pokémon known for its weak stats and flopping behavior. It evolves into Gyarados at level 20.

name: Gyarados
info: Gyarados evolves from Magikarp starting at level 20. It is known for its fierce temper and powerful attacks.

name: Lapras
info: Lapras is a Water/Ice-type Pokémon known for its gentle nature and ability to ferry people across water. It evolves from a Larvitar in later generations.

name: Ditto
info: Ditto is a Normal-type Pokémon known for its ability to transform into other Pokémon. It is used in breeding and can evolve into a number of other Pokémon in later generations.

name: Eevee
info: Eevee is a Normal-type Pokémon known for its multiple evolutions. It can evolve into various types including Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, and more.

name: Vaporeon
info: Vaporeon is one of Eevee's evolutions, evolving when exposed to a Water Stone. It is known for its aquatic abilities and its elegant appearance.

name: Jolteon
info: Jolteon is another evolution of Eevee, evolving when exposed to an Electric Stone. It is known for its speed and electric attacks.

name: Flareon
info: Flareon evolves from Eevee when exposed to a Fire Stone. It is known for its fiery temperament and powerful fire attacks.

name: Porygon
info: Porygon is a Normal-type Pokémon known for its digital, polygonal appearance. It can evolve into Porygon2 and Porygon-Z in later generations.

name: Omanyte
info: Omanyte is a Rock/Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Omastar. It is known for its spiral shell and ancient appearance.

name: Omastar
info: Omastar evolves from Omanyte starting at level 40. It is known for its fossil origins and powerful tentacle attacks.

name: Kabuto
info: Kabuto is a Rock/Water-type Pokémon that evolves into Kabutops. It is known for its ancient, shell-like appearance.

name: Kabutops
info: Kabutops evolves from Kabuto starting at level 40. It is known for its sharp, scythe-like claws and aggressive nature.

name: Aerodactyl
info: Aerodactyl is a Rock/Flying-type Pokémon known for its prehistoric appearance and flying abilities. It evolves from the Fossil Pokémon.

name: Snorlax
info: Snorlax is a Normal-type Pokémon known for its enormous size and its tendency to sleep in inconvenient places. It evolves from Munchlax.

name: Articuno
info: Articuno is a Legendary Ice/Flying-type Pokémon known for its majestic appearance and control over ice. It is often found in the game's Legendary encounters.

name: Zapdos
info: Zapdos is a Legendary Electric/Flying-type Pokémon known for its powerful electric attacks. It is a key part of the trio of Legendary Birds.

name: Moltres
info: Moltres is a Legendary Fire/Flying-type Pokémon known for its fiery plumage and ability to control flames. It completes the trio of Legendary Birds.

name: Dratini
info: Dratini is a Dragon-type Pokémon that evolves into Dragonair starting at level 30. It is known for its serpentine form and is part of the Dragon family.

name: Dragonair
info: Dragonair evolves from Dratini starting at level 30 and evolves into Dragonite. It is known for its graceful appearance and dragon-like abilities.

name: Dragonite
info: Dragonite evolves from Dragonair starting at level 55. It is known for its incredible strength and flying abilities, making it a powerful and versatile Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo
info: Mewtwo is a Psychic-type Legendary Pokémon created from the DNA of Mew. It is known for its immense psychic powers and its role as a powerful antagonist in various Pokémon games and media.

name: Mew
info: Mew is a Psychic-type Mythical Pokémon known for its ability to learn any move and its role as a genetic ancestor of all Pokémon. It is often associated with rare and special events.
